NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_isis_network_group_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork-NGPF

This procedure creates/modifies/deletes ISIS route(s) to a particular simulated ISIS router Ixia Interface. The user can configure the properties of the ISIS routes.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_isis_network_group_config

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

This option represents the handle the user *must* pass to the "emulation_isis_network_group_config" procedure. This option specifies on which ISIS router to configure the ISIS topology. The ISIS router handle(s) are returned by the procedure "emulation_isis_config" when configuring ISIS routers on the Ixia interface.

DEFAULT

 None

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF [M]

DESCRIPTION

Mode of the procedure call. Valid choices are: create modify delete.

Valid options are:

create

modify

delete

DEFAULT

 None

-type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Valid options are:

custom

hub-and-spoke

tree

ipv4-prefix

ipv6-prefix

fat-tree

linear
